00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:46.000
We need Black Gram, Red Kidney Beans, Onion, Tomato, Curd, Fresh Cream, Butter, Coriander powder, Turmeric powder, Red chili powder, Garam masala, Salt, Milk and Honey to prepare Dal Makhani.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Mix black gram and red kidney beans and pressure cook for 25 minutes on medium flame.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Here, you can see boiled Dal in this bowl.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:12.000
Now, seperate half of your boiled Dal in a pan; and mash it.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:25.000
Mix this mashed Dal in remaining boiled Dal. Let this mixture boil on low flame.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:34.000
Now add beaten curd in Dal.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:44.000
Also add fresh cream, milk and honey in Dal.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:57.000
Let Dal boil continuously for 15 more minutes on low flame.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:04.000
Meanwhile, we will prepare tomato-onion puree in a separate pan.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:18.000
For puree, take butter in a pan and heat it. Then, add ground onion-tomato mixture in it, and let it cook for few minutes.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:34.000
Now add turmeric powder, coriander powder, red chili powder and salt in puree; and let it cook for few more minutes, till butter comes at surface of the puree.

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:44.000
Now, add this puree in Dal; and let your Dal boil for another 5 minutes.

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:52.000
Your Dal Makhani is ready. Sprinkle Garam Masala over it when serve hot.

